- It features low‑compression mastering that preserves micro‑dynamics and transient snap — this directly aligns with my dislike of loudness‑flattening compression and my preference for preserved transients, audible breaths and replayable groove.
- Upfront yet natural drums and restrained guitars indicate preserved rhythmic punch without aggressive, fatiguing coloration. That satisfies my need for tight drums/bass and studio polish while avoiding harshness.
